cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.HC 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for detecting disfluencies in spoken dialogue. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves the use of neural networks and multi-task learning, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper focuses on improving the performance of dialogue systems, which could fall under cs.SD (Sound and Dialogue) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
